            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>Tabish ("we," "our," or "us") builds and publishes mobile applications for iOS. This Privacy Policy applies to all apps published under the Tabish developer account on the Apple App Store. We are committed to protecting your privacy and being transparent about how our apps handle your information.</p>

            <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
            <p>Our apps are designed with privacy in mind. We collect minimal information:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>App usage data</strong> — stored locally on your device only (progress, preferences, settings, history)</li>
                <li><strong>Purchase information</strong> — processed securely through Apple's App Store. We never see your payment details.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Information We Do NOT Collect</h2>
            <p>Our apps do not collect, store, or transmit:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Personal information (name, email, phone number, address)</li>
                <li>Location data</li>
                <li>Device identifiers or advertising IDs</li>
                <li>Browsing history or cross-app tracking data</li>
                <li>Photos, contacts, or calendar data (unless the app's core feature requires it, and only with your explicit permission)</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Data Storage</h2>
            <p>All your personal data (progress, settings, preferences, entries, logs) is stored <strong>locally on your device</strong> using Apple's built-in data storage frameworks (SwiftData). We do not operate any servers or cloud databases. Your data remains on your device and under your complete control at all times.</p>

            <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
            <p>Our apps do not integrate any third-party services including:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>No analytics SDKs (no Google Analytics, Firebase, Mixpanel, etc.)</li>
                <li>No advertising networks or ad SDKs</li>
                <li>No social media SDKs</li>
                <li>No crash reporting services</li>
                <li>No tracking or fingerprinting tools</li>
            </ul>
            <p>The only external service our apps interact with is <strong>Apple's App Store</strong> for processing in-app purchases. This is handled entirely by Apple according to their own privacy policies.</p>

            <h2>In-App Purchases</h2>
            <p>Some of our apps offer a one-time premium purchase (typically $2.99 USD). All payment processing is handled securely by Apple through the App Store. We do not collect, store, or have access to your payment information, credit card details, or Apple ID. Purchase verification is done on-device through Apple's StoreKit framework.</p>

            <h2>Tracking</h2>
            <p>We do <strong>not</strong> track you. Our apps do not:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Use the AppTrackingTransparency framework</li>
                <li>Collect IDFA (Identifier for Advertisers)</li>
                <li>Link data collected from the app with third-party data for advertising</li>
                <li>Share collected data with data brokers</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
            <p>Our apps do not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13. All data is stored locally on the device. No account creation is required to use any of our apps. Our education-focused apps (such as Math Tables, SpellBee, and KidTimer) are designed to be safe for children of all ages.</p>

            <h2>Health Data</h2>
            <p>Some of our apps (such as HydroLog, MoodTrack, IntermitFast) may optionally integrate with Apple Health (HealthKit). Health data is accessed only with your explicit permission, used only within the app for its intended purpose, and is never transmitted to external servers. You can revoke Health access at any time in your device Settings.</p>

            <h2>Camera &amp; Photos</h2>
            <p>Some of our apps (such as ColorPalette, CalorieEstimate) may request access to your camera or photo library. This access is used only for the app's core functionality, is requested only when needed, and the data stays on your device. No photos or camera data are transmitted externally.</p>

            <h2>Your Rights</h2>
            <p>You have the right to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Delete the app and all associated local data at any time</li>
                <li>Control notification permissions through your device Settings</li>
                <li>Control camera, photo, health, and location permissions through your device Settings</li>
                <li>Request information about our data practices by contacting us</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Data Deletion</h2>
            <p>Since all data is stored locally on your device, you can delete all app data at any time by simply deleting the app. No data remains on any server because we do not operate any servers.</p>

            <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated "Last Updated" date. We encourage you to review this page periodically.</p>

